  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind feature\r\n\r\nCurrently, the volume controller's block volume mount generator function makes assumptions how internal volume plugins work and mount block devices.  While these assumptions are OK for most internal volume plugins, they won't work for the CSI, which delegates further to external CSI drivers.  \r\n\r\nThe volume controller mount generator function should be refactored to delegate the Mapping decision to the BlockVolumeMapper interface implemented by the internal volume plugins.\r\n\r\n/sig storage\r\n",
